  "stem": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"2 script l plus 2 w less than or equals 27\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>w</mi><mo>&#8804;</mo><mn>27</mn></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A rectangle has length&nbsp;<math alttext=\"script l\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math> and width <math alttext=\"w\"><mi>w</mi>\n</math>. The inequality gives the possible values of&nbsp;<math alttext=\"script l\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math> and <math alttext=\"w\"><mi>w</mi>\n</math> for which the perimeter of this rectangle is less than or equal to <math alttext=\"27\"><mn>27</mn>\n</math>. Which statement is the best interpretation of <math alttext=\"left parenthesis script l comma w right parenthesis equals left parenthesis 8 comma 3 right parenthesis\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>w</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> in this context?</p>",
